      "name": "Applicability constraint: centrifugal VAD hemolysis prediction domain",
      "description": "The CFD model is applicable only to continuous-flow centrifugal blood pumps with specific speed Ns between 1500 and 4500 rpm·(gpm)^0.5·(ft)^-0.75, operating with anticoagulated human blood or validated blood analogue fluids. The hemolysis prediction methodology is scoped to power-law Giersiepen-Wurzinger formulations calibrated against FDA generic pump data. Extrapolation to axial-flow pumps, pulsatile devices, or non-Newtonian blood substitutes is outside this COU.",
      "inScopeDomain": "Centrifugal VAD, Ns 1500–4500, anticoagulated blood, steady-state operating points"
